reviewText:
if you're on Windows 7 x64 or higher, just know that this one's a gamble. crysis is an excellent game, but it is loaded with needless/annoying DRM, crashes easily, and doesn't play that well w/ Windows these days. i've often had to tweak/patch older games to get them up and running well, but Crysis has been an unusually stubborn one for me.

if you get it working, or are lucky enough not to have issues, be aware that you will still be installing PunkBuster DRM and some outdated bs called Gamespy Console in order to play. (or else spend time figuring out ways to disable and get around them.)

if you can get this one running, it's a great game. but getting it running properly can be a major headache.
